Task:8       

Input:
SHOW DATABASES;
USE database_name;
SHOW TABLES;
CREATE DATABASE new_database;
CREATE TABLE my_table (
    id INT,
    name STRING,
    age INT
);
LOAD DATA LOCAL INPATH '/path/to/datafile.csv' OVERWRITE INTO TABLE my_table;
SELECT * FROM my_table WHERE age > 25;
INSERT INTO TABLE my_table VALUES (1, 'John', 30);
DESCRIBE my_table;
DROP TABLE my_table;
Steps:
Hive Basic Commands: 
Show Databases: SHOW DATABASES; 
Use Database: 
USE database_name; Show Tables: 
SHOW TABLES; 
Create a Database: 
CREATE DATABASE new_database; 

Create a Table: 
CREATE TABLE my_table ( 
    id INT, 
    name STRING,     age INT 
); 
Load Data into a Table: 
LOAD DATA LOCAL INPATH '/path/to/datafile.csv' OVERWRITE INTO TABLE my_table; Query Data: 
SELECT * FROM my_table WHERE age > 25; Insert Data into a Table: 
INSERT INTO TABLE my_table VALUES (1, 'John', 30); Describe Table: 
DROP TABLE my_table;
